					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of 368 folios; written in Sefardi square script, first quarter of 14th century, punctuated.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment codex. </support>
								<extent>368 folios<dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>240</height>
										<width>210</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>185</height>
										<width>160</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>368 folios (+ 1 unfoliated paper flyleaf at the beginning and 4 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the end). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Originally quires of 6 leaves, but at a later re-binding the quires have been rendered indeterminate. </p>
									<p>Catchwords at the end of quires. </p>
								</collation>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="3" ruledLines="32" writtenLines="32">
									<p>Folio 1 is cut off most part. Folios 1 and 4 are later additions.
 </p>
									<p>Complete ruling with hard-point. Pricking in outer and inner margins, quire by quire, on recto. </p>
									<p>Uniform layout, last line of text written ouside ruling. </p>
									<p>Heading on each leaf. </p>
									<p>Hebrew foliation from folio 5, starting with 2 until the end of the Pentateuch (folio 99).
 </p>
									<p>In the colophon (folio 184), the name of the patron has been erased. The original date <date calendar="Hebrew">5060 </date>[<date calendar="Gregorian">1300</date>] has been erased and overwritten as <date calendar="Hebrew">5006 </date>[<date calendar="Gregorian">1246</date>].
The same scribe copied two other bibles in Toledo: Sassoon Collection (MS 508 dated 1307, MS 1208 dated 1334). </p>
									<p>Numerous decorations: full-page miniature of the Temple implements, 5 full borders of geometric design, masorah in the margins written in microghraphical form, 6 full-page panels of masorah magna in micrographical design, numerous decorated parashah signs. </p>
									<p>Masorah magna occupies two lines at the top and three lines at the bottom of each page.  </p>
									<p>Joshua, Isaiah, Psalms, and Chronicles begin a new leaf, and Jeremiah begins a new column. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Sefardi square script of the beginning of 14th century, punctuated. </summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="scribe">Yosef ben Yudah ben Merwas</name>: inscribed with his name in the colophon, Toledo, <date calendar="Hebrew">Iyyar 5060</date> [<date calendar="Gregorian">1300</date>] (folio 184r). </p>
							<p>Erased inscription (folio 4r). </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Sulaiman ben Shemu᾿el (?) ben Ḥayim</name>: inscribed with his name as the seller in an Arabic purchase note, <date calendar="Gregorian">1450</date> (folio 99v). </p>
							<p>Judeo-Arabic note, partially obliterated (folio 368v). </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Shalom ben Yosef Ḥayim [ .. ]  Levi</name>: inscribed with his name in an owner's inscription, 18th century (folio 184r). </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Musi 'n Salem al-Gamal</name>: inscribed with his name in an owner's inscription, 18th century (folio 184r). </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Judah 'n Musi</name>: inscribed with his name in an unclear purchase note, undated (folio 186v). </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Yudah Kamal</name>: inscribed with his name in an owner's inscription, undated (folio 5r).</p>
						</additions>
